name: Clark County PH- COVID Vaccine Site
address: Ridgefield High School 2630 S Hillhurst Rd, Ridgefield WA, 98642
info:
The Ridgefield High School vaccination site is providing the Johnson & Johnson vaccine. The Johnson & Johnson vaccine requires only one dose; you will not need to return for a second dose.

Please do not arrive more than 10 minutes before your scheduled appointment. Arriving too early can lead to longer waiting times. 

You will be asked to remain at the vaccination site for 15 to 30 minutes after being vaccinated. Medical personnel will be monitoring you for possible reactions. Severe reactions are rare. 

What to bring:
•	Identification: If you have identification or some other proof of your date of birth, please bring it. This helps to ensure registration information is accurate. But ID is not required for vaccination. 
•	Insurance card: If you have insurance, please bring your insurance card. Your insurance will be billed for the vaccine administration fee. Insurance coverage is not required. If you do not have insurance, you will still be vaccinated at no cost.
•	Face covering: Face coverings must be worn while at the COVID-19 vaccination site. 
•	Please wear a short-sleeved shirt or shirt with loose sleeves that can be pulled up. You will receive your COVID-19 vaccine in your upper arm. 

El lugar de vacunación en la Escuela Ridgefield High School  está proporcionando la vacuna Johnson & Johnson. La vacuna Johnson & Johnson sólo es una dosis; usted no tendrá que regresar por una segunda dosis.

Por favor, no llegue más de 10 minutos antes de su cita. Llegar con demasiada antelación puede causar tiempos de espera más largos.

Se le pedirá que permanezca en el centro de vacunación de 15 a 30 minutos después de ser vacunado. El personal médico le vigilará para detectar posibles reacciones. Las reacciones graves son poco frecuentes.  

Qué debe traer:
•	Identificación: Si tiene un documento de identitificación, o documento con fecha de nacimiento, por favor tráigalo. Esto ayuda a asegurar que la información de registro es correcta. Pero no es necesario presentar un documento de identidad para la vacunación.  
•	Tarjeta de seguro: Si tiene seguro, por favor traiga su tarjeta de seguro. Su seguro será facturado por la tarifa de administración de la vacuna. La cobertura del seguro no es necesaria. Si no tiene seguro, se le vacunará igualmente sin costo alguno.
•	Prenda para cubrirse la cara: Debe llevar una prenda para cubrirse la cara mientras esté en el centro de vacunación de COVID-19.  
•	Por favor, lleve una camisa de mangas cortas o una camisa con mangas sueltas que se puedan subir. Usted recibirá la vacuna contra la COVID-19 en la parte superior del brazo.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
address: 1235 North Post St. Suite 201, Spokane WA, 99205
info:
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. *** All patients 12 years old and older can register regardless of phase. (If 12-17 years old must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. Enter the building at the time of your appointment only. 
***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***

name: Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine - COVID Vaccine Clinic
info:
At the Hawker Center, we provide a warm oasis of peace and comfort, treating our patients and their stories with patience and respect. Imagine a spa-like atmosphere where a highly-trained doctor or nurse is administrating the COVID19 vaccination. That’s the Hawker Center difference.
***We currently are providing the 1st and 2nd doses of MODERNA.*** Please sign up for an appointment time.  Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay for 15 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction.***If you would like to find out more information about our clinic, please visit our website at www.hawkerhealth.com***

name: Community Vaccination Center at Bellingham Technical College
address: Bellingham Technical College, 3028 Lindbergh Avenue – Building G, Bellingham WA, 98225
info:
College Days One and Done (Janssen) Clinic!  Be prepared for the fall semester vaccination requirement with a single vaccination visit.  All adults 18 and over are welcome to register and attend - first come first served.  Walk-ins are welcome.

If you are having difficulty signing up via the web-site, or need additional assistance, please call our Vaccine Access Scheduler Line at 360-778-6075 on Monday through Friday from 8:30 AM to 4:00 PM.
